<promed@promedmail.org>
[Protists are a category of microbes having a very wide range. They may be
very complicated organisms. Protists include slime molds, protozoa and
primitive algae. These are single cell organisms that have their DNA
contained within a nucleus (eukaryotic).
These organisms are not truly plant or animal, but something in between,
and are rather difficult to work with in the laboratory, which may be the
reason more research has not been done. It is understandable this community
is upset. - Mod.TG]
